# Qwertystock / Way Dependencies

Qwertystock production, Way-hosted services, support chat, domain automation,
and experimental adjacent products share infrastructure. Inspect dependency
boundaries before changing routing, deployment, DNS, service units, or shared
rules.

- Main Qwertystock sales site is `https://qwertystock.com` on
  `145.239.0.57`.
- Way host is `https://way.qwertystock.com` on `37.187.57.177`; it is shared
  infrastructure, not the main sales site.
- Way services can depend on the local/remote `qwertystock` app, support chat,
  nginx routes, systemd units, and domain automation. Read current state before
  editing.
- Prefer additive routing and service changes on Way. Do not disturb unrelated
  services such as support chat, Detectron, RF2, static `/app`, or existing
  `qwertystock-way.service` routes.
- Domain, DNS, mail, and Resend work must go through the established
  `qwertystock_domain_api` safety workflow when that integration is explicitly
  in scope. Otherwise, leave `R:\M_plus_front\qwertystock_domain_api` untouched.
- Never bypass shared service dependency checks just because a change appears
  frontend-only or scaffold-only.
- Never print or commit secrets, credentialized remotes, private keys, tokens,
  cookies, production env contents, or raw server credential files.
